commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to edit persons to events
commitResults.messageBody:
Update edit_meeting command: If editing the event with a valid name, it will add the person name to the existing associated persons. E.g: if an event (1) has Bob already assigned to it, edit_meeting 1 n/John would add John to the list instead of replacing it. This makes the adding of associated persons easier.
Update corresponding success and failure messages.

commitResults.messageTitle: Link edit person to editing events
commitResults.messageBody: When a person's name is changed(as this is the person's unique identifier), it will also update any corresponding events that have the person previously assigned to it. Events that do not have the person assigned to it will be ignored.

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to unassign persons from events
commitResults.messageBody:
By using the command edit_meeting u/[UNASSSIGN PERSON]... the user will be able to unassign the person(s) previously associated with the event.

There are 2 exceptions to this:
1. If the specified person does not exist, an error message is displayed
2. If the specified person exists but has not even been assigned in the first place, another error message is displayed.

Updated corresponding success and error messages.
